'''Oona Castilla Chaplin''' (born 4 June 1986) is a Spanish actress, dancer and ballerina. Born in Madrid, Spain, she also grew up in Switzerland. From the age of 15 she attended [[wikipedia:Gordonstoun|Gordonstoun School]] in Scotland and later attended [[wikipedia:RADA|RADA]] in London. Chaplin's parents are British-American actressÂ [[wikipedia:Geraldine Chaplin|Geraldine Chaplin]] and Chilean cinematographer Patricio Castilla. Her [[wikipedia:namesake|namesake]] is herÂ maternal grandmotherÂ [[wikipedia:Oona O'Neill|Oona O'Neill]], Irish American playwright [[wikipedia:Eugene O'Neill|Eugene O'Neill]]'s onlyÂ daughter and British comedian and filmmaker [[wikipedia:Charlie Chaplin|Charlie Chaplin]]'s fourth wife.&lt;ref&gt;Holly Williams, Holly (July 16, 2011). [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/funny-girl-the-notso-silent-star-oona-chaplin-2312991.html Funny girl: The not-so silent star Oona Chaplin]. The Independent.&lt;/ref&gt;

Her first screen appearances was on the British drama series ''[[wikipedia:Spooks|Spooks]]'' in 2007. She had a minor part in the ''[[wikipedia:James Bond|James Bond]]'' movie ''[[wikipedia:Quantum of Solace|Quantum of Solace]]''. Most recently she had a recurring role as upper class housewife turned TV cooking show host Marnie Madden on the BBC drama series ''[[wikipedia:The Hour|The Hour]]'', and she appears in the BBC series ''[[wikipedia:Sherlock (TV series)|Sherlock]]'' as John Watson's girlfriend Jeanette.

In an interview with ''[[wikipedia:The Daily Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]'' that was published on August 11, 2011, Chaplin confirmed she had secured a role in the second season.&lt;ref&gt;Tyzack, Anna (August 11, 2011). [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/my-perfect-weekend/8695705/My-perfect-weekend-Oona-Chaplin.html My perfect weekend: Oona Chaplin]. The Daily Telegraph.&lt;/ref&gt; This was later suggested to be [[Jeyne Westerling]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.comicbookmovie.com/fansites/rorschachsrants/news/?a=44507 ComicBookMovie.com]&lt;/ref&gt; She joined the cast as a guest star in the [[Season 2|second season]]. However, her character introduces herself as [[Talisa Maegyr]] rather than Jeyne when she first appears in &quot;[[Garden of Bones]].&quot;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Garden of Bones]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; It was later revealed that the original plan had been for Chaplin to play Jeyne, but the character was dramatically changed in rewrites. Eventually [[George R.R. Martin]] himself suggested renaming her and came up with her character's new name.&lt;ref&gt;Ryan, Maureen (September 4, 2012). [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/04/game-of-thrones-season-3-characters_n_1854918.html 'Game of Thrones' Season 3 Characters And Scoop From Creator George R.R. Martin]. Huffington Post.&lt;/ref&gt;

Chaplin has described herself as a &quot;massive fan&quot; of both ''Game of Thrones'' as well as the ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]'' book series prior to her own casting.&lt;ref&gt;(April 19, 2012). [http://winteriscoming.net/2012/04/interview-with-oona-chaplin Interview with Oona Chaplin]. WinterIsComing.Net.&lt;/ref&gt;
